        <h1>「 Modeling Making 」</h1>
        <h2 class="subtitle">\Bumblebee</h2>
        <div class="T__wrap">
            <img class="T__wrap-bg" src="images/work6/qiche.jpg" alt="IMG">

            <div class="layout-1">
                <p><em>Made with greasy car model.</em>
                    <br>
                    In fact, the beginning to know that this course is a compulsory time, many students around some of the emotions complained. After all, there are far fewer students who choose to design their cars for the future. We have repeatedly questioned the significance of this course, laborious, nor necessarily pleasing.<br>
                    We understand that there are many production methods to choose from during the model making stage. Choosing the clay model as the first choice is determined by the particularity of the car styling design and the characteristics of the sludge itself. <br>
                    First, the relatively complex car shape, which consists of a combination of smooth surfaces, calls for a way to create flexible surfaces of all kinds. Compared with other methods, sludge can be easily scraped into any shape, which is very suitable for the performance of automotive surfaces. Second, the car shape design often has a repetitive process, the model to do repeated scrutiny, which requires the model itself has plasticity. The characteristics of sludge model exactly meet the requirements: Unlike ordinary mud, the sludge after heating, the hardness will be reduced rapidly, get very good flexibility, especially suitable for remodeling; temperature drop, the hardness and recovery quickly, suitable Details of the portrayal. This process can be repeated many times, without affecting the quality of the sludge itself. Thirdly, the car's exterior design is very demanding on the smoothness of the surface texture. The surface of ordinary mud can not achieve that smoothness, while the clay texture is delicate and smooth, meeting the near-harsh surface requirements. From the production time point of view, the sludge model is a relatively quick one.<br> 
                    Therefore, it naturally becomes the main model making method of the current automobile modeling design.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
